article.headline: Albany (NY) 86, New Hampshire 63
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Logan Aronhalt scored 21 points while Mike Black and Gerardo Suero added 17 apiece for Albany (N.Y.) in an 86-63 win over New Hampshire on Wednesday night. The Great Danes (10-7, 2-1 America East Conference), who have won four of their last five, were never really threatened in this one. They led from wire to wire, opening on a 21-10 run and taking a 19-point lead at the break. Albany outscored the Wildcats 47-43 in the second half to seal it. The Great Danes outshot the Wildcats from the floor, 49.2 percent (32 of 65) to 36.4 percent (20 of 55). They also outrebounded New Hampshire 47-29. Patrick Konan scored 13 points to lead New Hampshire (5-8, 0-2), which has lost a season-high three straight. Brian Benson added 12 points and Alvin Abreu chipped in with 11 for the Wildcats.
